A vintage 1980s-style illustration showing a split scene: on the left, a sleek corporate office with a lone worker at a terminal surrounded by floating clock fragments and small pill-sized capsules dissolving in the air; on the right, a warm classroom space with interconnected pathways, books, and layered screens forming an elaborate web. The two worlds are divided by a cracked bridge made of floppy disks and early computer components, with tangled cables attempting to connect both sides but falling short into a misty void. Muted earth tones and faded amber screens contrast with chalk-dust atmosphere and worn wood textures. The composition emphasizes disconnection and missed opportunity, with empty chairs on both sides suggesting untapped potential.
